In response to your message sent  21 March 1986 1126-PST (Friday)

Ron,

The set of QTYPES includes all TYPEs.  Thus SOA, MX, A, etc are all
valid as QTYPES.  (To keep our sanity, we also assign identical numeric
codes for TYPE A and QTYPE A, etc). QTYPEs also include some things that
aren't TYPEs, e.g. *, and MAILA, and MAILB.  Since you can always ask
for a particular TYPE, there is no point in having a QTYPE that just
returns one TYPE (except, perhaps, for future expansion).  Since our
purpose in going from MD and MF to MX was to coalesce these RRs into a
single type, it doesn't seem useful to keep MAILA for the future, and
requiring existing implementations to change MAILA didn't seem useful
either.

The numeric code for MX is 15 decimal.

By the way, is the BIND mailing list a subset of NAMEDROPPERS?  If not,
why not?  I know I have been guilty of copying both in the past, but is
it necessary?  (Answers to me or the BIND list only please.)

paul
